<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/1002: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-24T16:00:00-04:00">August 24, 1938—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following for Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>296. “Shanghai’s 1152, August 22, 7 p.m., in regard to Whangpoo
                                    Conservancy Board. The Department desires that, after
                                    consultation with your British and French colleagues, and if and
                                    when they are prepared to take separate but similar action, you
                                    approach the Japanese Foreign Office, in such manner as you may
                                    deem appropriate, substantially along the lines indicated in
                                    paragraph 1 of the telegram under reference.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Repeat to Chungking and mail copy to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>